name: NonEmergencyAmbulanceTransportQualifyingProcedure
title: Non Emergency Ambulance Transport Qualifying Procedure
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Dialysis, wound care, radiation therapy, chemotherapy, prosthetic care, orthotic care, and imaging.),(Data Element Scope: Procedures that are not to be performed in a patient's home that may justify non-emergency ambulance transport to the service performing location as defined by the US Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services.),(Inclusion Criteria: Dialysis, wound care, radiation therapy, chemotherapy, prosthetic care, orthotic care, and imaging.),(Exclusion Criteria: Procedures that may be performed in an outpatient or ambulatory setting other than those listed in the inclusion criteria.)
